init_text: Following World War III, all the nations of the world agreed to 50 years of strict isolation from one another in order to prevent additional conflicts. 50 years later, the United States comes out of exile, only to learn that no one else went into isolation.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: The United States is now the only remaining superpower, and must face the challenges of a new world.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: The United States has two options:

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: The United States can either stay in isolation for another 50 years, or can try to re-establish contact with the rest of the world.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: The United States must decide which option to take.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: If the United States stays in isolation, the country will continue to prosper and grow.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: The United States will be able to develop new technology and advance the country without the interference of other countries.
